description:
Panel - "Macular Collective research on art, science, technology, and perception" at the 2016 Gray Area Festival.

Macular (Eric Parren, Nicky Assmann, Joris Strijbos) is an initiative of a group of artists who share a collective interest in art, science, technology, and perception. One of the ongoing research topics is the creation and manipulation of emergent systems and the possibilities for composition that arise from them. The artists aim to create their own abstract language that is mostly based on rule-sets within self-built systems. Macular aims for a minimalistic aesthetic through a continuous exploration of the basic characteristic properties of the media they use. Whether they are cultivated systems or natural phenomena, the medium gets stripped down to the essence of the medium itself. Moderated by Sophie Lamparter.

The Gray Area Festival is four days of conference, performances, workshops, and exhibitions to discuss the impact of art and technology on culture. More at http://grayareafestival.io
